This deployment introduces Amazon's latest Nova 2 class models with advanced reasoning capabilities and Anthropic's most capable Claude 4.6 class models (Sonnet and Opus) to the organisation's approved Bedrock catalogue.
The bedrock:InvokeTool permission for Nova's built-in system tools (Web Grounding, Code Interpreter) is restricted by default and will require a separate risk assessment and namespace-level approval.


Major Highlight: Enablement of Amazon Nova 2 class (Lite, Sonic) and Anthropic Claude 4.6 class (Sonnet 4.6, Opus 4.6) foundation models across all Bedrock-provisioned accounts, bringing the latest generation of reasoning, multimodal, and agentic AI capabilities to the organisation's approved model catalogue.
